TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Miner Sentence Completion Scale: An Appraisal
AU  - Brief, Arthur P.
AU  - Aldag, Ramon J.
AU  - Chacko, Thomas I.
Y1  - 1977/12/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255362
DO  - 10.5465/255362
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 635
EP  - 643
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Selected psychometric properties of the Miner Sentence Completion Scale (MSCS) were evaluated. In particular, the degree to which the MSCS converges with England's Personal Values Questionnaire (PVQ) was assessed, the convergent and discriminant validity of three MSCS subscales with three subscales of the Ghiselli Self-Description Inventory (SDI) was examined, and inter-scorer reliability for the MSCS was considered. No significant relationship between the MSCS and the PVQ was detected; limited evidence of convergent and discriminant validity between the MSCS and SDI was found; and questions were raised regarding the reliability of the procedures used for scoring the MSCS.
AB  - Selected psychometric properties of the Miner Sentence Completion Scale (MSCS) were evaluated. In particular, the degree to which the MSCS converges with England's Personal Values Questionnaire (PVQ) was assessed, the convergent and discriminant validity of three MSCS subscales with three subscales of the Ghiselli Self-Description Inventory (SDI) was examined, and inter-scorer reliability for the MSCS was considered. No significant relationship between the MSCS and the PVQ was detected; limited evidence of convergent and discriminant validity between the MSCS and SDI was found; and questions were raised regarding the reliability of the procedures used for scoring the MSCS.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255362
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255362
Y2  - 2026/04/24
