JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 644
EP  - 655
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Attitudes toward 4/40 work schedules were studied for 1,401 mid-level exempt personnel who worked a 5/40 schedule. Significant relationships were found between 4/40 attitudes and organizational, individual, environmental, and affective variables. However, only a small proportion (7 percent) of the 4/40 attitude variance was accounted for. It was suggested that decisions to adopt 4/40 schedules should include consideration of technological and market factors.
AB  - Attitudes toward 4/40 work schedules were studied for 1,401 mid-level exempt personnel who worked a 5/40 schedule. Significant relationships were found between 4/40 attitudes and organizational, individual, environmental, and affective variables. However, only a small proportion (7 percent) of the 4/40 attitude variance was accounted for. It was suggested that decisions to adopt 4/40 schedules should include consideration of technological and market factors.
