N2  - A model of behavioral choice based on expectancy theory was tested in the context of budget allocation decision making by academic deans. Hypotheses dealing with both the direction and magnitude of the criterion behavior received moderate support. Two methods of scaling outcome affect led to similar results. Weighting expectancy by affect did not account for greater criterion variance.
AB  - A model of behavioral choice based on expectancy theory was tested in the context of budget allocation decision making by academic deans. Hypotheses dealing with both the direction and magnitude of the criterion behavior received moderate support. Two methods of scaling outcome affect led to similar results. Weighting expectancy by affect did not account for greater criterion variance.
