SP  - 669
EP  - 676
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the survey results from a study pertaining to the use of quantitative techniques in production and operations management. Over 60% of the respondents said they did not use quantitative techniques. Approximately 25% reported using only 7 of the 19 techniques. A portion of the quantitative techniques are not considered to have high applicability in production and operations management. Among the techniques considered relevant to production and operations management are simulation, queuing theory, network analysis, and inventory models.
